[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(25) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then said Jehu.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he said.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bidkar.—The Syriac gives Bar-dĕkar, “son of stabbing,” i.e., “stabber,” “slayer” a very suitable name for Jehu’s squire. The Hebrew name is, therefore, a contraction of Ben-dekar. (Comp. Bedan, “son of Dan,” i.e., Danite, 1Samuel 12:11; and Bedad, “son of Hadad,” in 1Chronicles 1:46.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Bidkar.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The Syriac gives ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Bar-dĕkar",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", “son of stabbing,” ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "i.e.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", “stabber,” “slayer” a very suitable name for Jehu’s squire. The Hebrew name is, therefore, a contraction of ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Ben-dekar",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". (Comp. Bedan, “son of Dan,” i.e., Danite, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 12:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; and Bedad, “son of Hadad,” in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 1:46",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Captain.—Adjutant, aide-de-camp, chief (2Kings 7:2).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Captain.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Adjutant, aide-de-camp,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " chief (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Kings 7:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Remember how that, when I and thou rode together.—This gives the sense of the Hebrew correctly. Literally, remember thou me and thee riding together. The word rendered “together” probably means riding side by side on horseback in attendance on the king. The Targum, vulg., and Kimchi interpret, riding together in the same chariot; Josephus, riding together in Ahab’s chariot behind him.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Remember how that, when I and thou rode together.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—This gives the sense of the Hebrew correctly. Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "remember thou me and thee riding together.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " The word rendered “together” probably means ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "riding side by side",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " on horseback in attendance on the king. The Targum, vulg., and Kimchi interpret, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "riding together in the same chariot",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; Josephus, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "riding together in Ahab’s chariot behind him.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord laid this burden upon him.—Rather, Jehovah uttered this (prophetic) utterance upon (i.e., about) him. (Comp. the oracle uttered by Elijah against Ahab when taking possession of Naboth’s vineyard, 1Kings 21:17, seq., 1Kings 21:29.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The Lord laid this burden upon him.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Jehovah uttered this",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
